This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel framework for matrix completion using deep learning methods, specifically graph neural networks. The paper also discusses the use of an extended variational auto-encoder structure, which is a common technique in deep learning. 

Additionally, the paper focuses on the problem of cold start recommendations, which is a common issue in recommendation systems. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which are both related to recommendation systems. 

The paper also mentions the use of attributes, which are a form of metadata, to learn embeddings for cold start users/items. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language), which both deal with the use of metadata and natural language processing in machine learning.
